cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for semantic part parsing of cars. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel mixture of graphical models, which involves dynamic programming, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of appearance consistency between segments within the same part suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of the method on a subset of PASCAL VOC 2010 car images and on the car subset of 3D Object Category dataset (CAR3D) suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of graphical models and dynamic programming suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
